{"body": "Maybe the implications aren't totally clear.\r\nCurrently all `method_missing` calls on `CollectionProxy` that are matched by the `DynamicFinderMatch` are executed twice. This is not only an unnecessary performance penalty, it can also lead to non-deterministic behavior.\r\n\r\nFor example, if you use `post.comments.find_by_foo` somewhere, it will run it twice. Same for `post.comments.find_or_create`. A `post.comments.find_or_initialize` will initialize a new object twice, returning the latest.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2801103", "created_at": "2011-11-19T21:49:19Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3610#issuecomment-2801103", "updated_at": "2011-11-19T21:49:19Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 3610, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/mlangenberg", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/49e98c4a13a5203ecff5d2d0774f8991?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F860320be12a1c050cd7731794e231bd3.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg/received_events", "gravatar_id": "49e98c4a13a5203ecff5d2d0774f8991", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "mlangenberg", "type": "User", "id": 992, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mlangenberg/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52383454bd3543c15100fb3c"}, "id": 2801103, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3610"}
